ainst our antidemocratic tendencies and reorient the nation toward the “more perfect union” of our Founders. Beem’s road map to restore our democracy draws on thinkers from Aristotle and Thomas Aquinas to James Madison, Hannah Arendt, Abraham Lincoln, and Franklin Delano Roosevelt. Empathetic and eminently reasonable, The Seven Democratic Virtues presents practical advice for what each of us can do to change the political discourse and save our democracy. This is necessary reading for our politics today—and in the future.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Civics & Citizenship.2bisacsh  aDemocracy.  aDemocrats.  aDonald Trump.  aPolitics.  aRepublicans.  aTribalism.  aVirtue.  acitizenship.  acivics.  acivil society.  aconservative.  aelectoral politics.  ahow to save democracy.  aliberal.  apartisanship.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2022 Englishz978311099451308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2022z9783110994407oZDB-23-PLW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn State University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z97831107669290 cprintz978027109394940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780271094366?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780271094366423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780271094366/original  a978-3-11-076692-9  Penn State University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-099389-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099451-3  EBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2022 Englishb2022 